@page
@model AboutModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About Sidebar Navigation";
}

<section class="content-card">
    <h2 class="h4">About this project</h2>
    <p class="mb-0">
        This stage of the module focuses on building professional sidebar navigation with Bootstrap.
        Students learn how to group links into collapsible sections, support deeper page hierarchies,
        and keep the current section visible across desktop and mobile layouts.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="row g-3 mt-1">
    <article class="col-md-6">
        <div class="content-card h-100">
            <h3 class="h5">What this module emphasizes</h3>
            <ul class="mb-0">
                <li>Sticky sidebar layout for larger page collections.</li>
                <li>Bootstrap Collapse for expandable sections.</li>
                <li>Bootstrap Offcanvas for mobile-friendly sidebar access.</li>
                <li>Route-aware active item highlighting.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </article>

    <article class="col-md-6">
        <div class="content-card h-100">
            <h3 class="h5">Quick links to test</h3>
            <ul class="mb-0">
                <li><a asp-page="/Docs/Guides/SidebarPatterns">Open a third-level Docs guide</a></li>
                <li><a asp-page="/Products/Category" asp-route-name="Computers">Open a Product Catalog child page</a></li>
                <li><a asp-page="/Blog/Archive" asp-route-year="2026">Open a Publishing archive page</a></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </article>
</section>

<section class="content-card mt-3">
    <h3 class="h5">Why sidebars matter</h3>
    <p class="mb-0">
        As projects grow, users need predictable navigation patterns. Well-structured sidebars improve discoverability,
        reduce confusion, and keep hierarchy visible even when there are many related pages.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-3 d-flex gap-2 flex-wrap">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" asp-page="/Docs/GettingStarted">Open docs section</a>
        <a class="btn btn-outline-primary" asp-page="/Products/Index">Explore product catalog</a>
        <a class="btn btn-outline-secondary" asp-page="/Contact">Open support page</a>
    </div>
</section>
